; PolyField Script
; Sends running clock, wind, and start list data to PolyField via UDP
;
; FinishLynx Scoreboard Configuration:
;   Script:        polyfield.lss
;   Port:          Network (UDP)
;   IP Address:    <PolyField machine IP>  (use 255.255.255.255 to broadcast on LAN)
;   Port Number:   5001
;   Running Time:  Normal
;   Results:       Off
;
; Clock packet format:  <time>|<eventName>
;   Running:      0:12.3|100m Men Final
;   Armed:        armed|100m Men Final
;   Stopped:      stopped:12.34|100m Men Final  (actual stop time included)
;   Time of day:  timeofday|<time string>
;   Wind reading: wind:+1.2|100m Men Final  (wind value in m/s, persists until next armed)
;
; Start list packet format:  startlist|<eventName>|<lane>|<bib>|<firstName>|<lastName>|<affiliation>
;   One packet is sent per athlete when the start list is loaded.
;   Lane will be empty if no lane assignments are set.
;
; Notes:
;   - Requires the NCP (Network COM Port) plugin (bundled free since FinishLynx 13.00)
;   - Time is formatted to tenths of a second while the clock is running (e.g. 0:12.3)
;   - PolyField firewall must allow inbound UDP on port 5001

;;TimeArmed
\11\01armed|
\13\02%s

;;TimeRunning
\11\01%s|
\13\02%s

;;TimeUpdate
\11\01%s|
\13\02%s

;;TimeStopped
\11\01stopped:%s|
\13\02%s

;;TimeOfDay
\11\01timeofday|
\13\02%s

;;WindReading
\11\01wind:%s|
\13\02%s

;;StartList
\11\01startlist|%e|%l|%i|%f|%s|%a
